		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Signal transducers and activators of transcription ( STATs ) are rapidly phosphorylated on tyrosine residues in response to cytokine and growth factor stimulation of cell surface receptors . <S>",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "STATs hereafter are translocated to the nucleus where they act as transcription factors . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "Recent reports suggest",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "that serine phosphorylation of STATs also is involved in the regulation of STAT-mediated gene transcription . <S>",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "Here , we studied the role of serine/threonine phosphatases in STAT3 signaling in human antigen-specific CD4(+) T cell lines and cutaneous T cell lymphoma lines , expressing a constitutively activated STAT3 . <S>",
			"relation": "ROOT",
			"tag": "Hypothesis-Objective"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "We show",
			"relation": "VERIFICATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "that an inhibitor of protein phosphatases ( PPs ) PP1/PP2A , calyculin A , induces ( i ) phosphorylation of STAT3 on serine and threonine residues , ( ii ) inhibition of STAT3 tyrosine phosphorylation and DNA binding activity , and ( iii ) relocation of STAT3 from the nucleus to the cytoplasm . <S>",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "Similar results were obtained with other PP2A inhibitors ( okadaic acid , endothall thioanhydride ) but not with inhibitors of PP1 ( tautomycin ) or PP2B ( cyclosporine A ) . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "Pretreatment with the broad serine/threonine kinase inhibitor staurosporine partly blocked the calyculin A-induced STAT3 phosphorylation ,",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "whereas inhibitors of serine/threonine kinases , such as mitogen-activated protein kinase-1 extracellular-regulated kinase-kinase , mitogen-activated protein p38 kinase , and phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase , did not . <S>",
			"relation": "COMPARISON",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "In conclusion , we provide evidence that PP2A plays a crucial role in the regulation of STAT3 phosphorylation and subcellular distribution in T cells . <S>",
			"relation": "CONCLUSION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "Moreover , our findings suggest",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "that the level of STAT3 phosphorylation is balanced between a staurosporine-sensitive kinase ( s ) and PP2A . <S>",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		}
	]
}